NAME
    Float::Util - Utilities related to floating point numbers

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.002 of Float::Util (from Perl
    distribution Float-Util), released on 2018-03-09.

SYNOPSIS
     use Float::Util qw(is_exact);

     is_exact("1.5"); # => true
     is_exact("0.1"); # => false

DESCRIPTION
FUNCTIONS
    None exported by default, but they are exportable.

  is_exact
    Usage: is_exact($strdec) => bool

    Test that a decimal number (a string) can be represented exactly as a
    floating point number.

